reviewText: As a long time fan of this 60s tv series, I ordered this set knowing well that it was not a retail-level product, so I took a gamble.  Well---I was pleasantly suprised at the product!  Great quality of recording/transfer.  No static or sound blurr---great image!---just like I remember it.  Didn't give it a 5-star because the discs didn't come printed with nice series images---but other than that, this is precisely what I was looking for.  The set comes with discs in individual envelopes and a fairly nice plastic storage case like the one in the picture, where you can organize each disc separatelly.  If you're a true fan of the Green Hornet, I'd say you'll be glad that you ordered this set.

reviewText: I don't know what they mean by no watermarks or logos in the description. But you can see the Action Channel logo pop up on the screen from time to time. It doesn't bother me at all. The picture quality of this set is much better than that of the Digi-pack. You don't get any of the extras the digi-pack has. But the one extra not available on the digi pack is a 5 min test pilot. This is strictly the entire Green Hornet series. Not even his Batman show appearance is here. But good news. Just click see all my reviews there is a batman dvd review. They are the ABC uncut episodes.
summary: IMPROVED PICTURE QUALITY OVER THE 4 DISC DIGI-PACK
